{"word":"H1319 - בָּשַׂר - bâsar - baw-sar' - Messenger","slug":"H1319","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בָּשַׂר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bâsar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>baw-sar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Messenger"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05E8; - ba&#x0302;s&#x0301;ar</b> - <i>baw-sar'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>be fresh</i>, that is, <i>full</i> (<i>rosy</i>, figuratively <i>cheerful</i>); to <i>announce</i> (glad news): - messenger, preach, publish, shew forth, (bear, bring, carry, preach, good, tell good) tidings."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1308\">H1308</a>, <a href=\"#/H1309\">H1309</a>, <a href=\"#/H1320\">H1320</a>"}]}